        <senderName>National Weather Service Atlanta GA</senderName>
        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 6:00PM EDT until July 24 at 9:00PM EDT by NWS Atlanta GA</headline>
        
        <description>
            At 600 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line extending from 
            near Marietta to near Atlanta, moving east at 25 mph. These storms have a 
            history of producing damaging winds and large hail.
            
            HAZARD: 70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
            SOURCE: Radar indicated.
            IMPACT: Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect considerable tree damage. 
            Wind damage is also likely to mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.
        </description>
        
        <instruction>
            For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building. 
            Large hail and damaging winds and continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring 
            with these storms. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading 
            killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.
        </instruction>
        
